discussion_comments.comment_body:
30xx/40xx series [could still benefit](https://github.com/Dao-AILab/flash-attention/issues/1049#issuecomment-2695283567) from FA3 if they install a prebuilt wheel from e.g.  https://windreamer.github.io/flash-attention3-wheels/, and then `import flash_attn_interface as flash_attn`. Tested on my 3090 (cuda 12.8) and works with this additional `else`.

```suggestion
    if torch.cuda.is_available():
        if torch.cuda.get_device_capability()[0] >= 9:
            flash_attn = get_kernel('varunneal/flash-attention-3').flash_attn_interface
        else:
            # If the kernel image is not available, try installing the wheel manually from https://windreamer.github.io/flash-attention3-wheels/
            import flash_attn_interface as flash_attn
```

